REFLECTION QUESTIONS:
1. Which fears showed up as most exaggerated when you examined them closely?
2. What prevention strategies felt most actionable?
3. How did considering repair options change your relationship to the fear?
4. What surprised you about the benefits of attempting?
5. What motivated you most when considering the cost of inaction?